    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-08-14T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-08-14T00:00:00-05:00" n="900"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d900">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 150.07/17</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The French Chargé d’Affaires</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_CJR1"
                        type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Clausse</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <dateline>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">French Embassy</hi>, <lb/>
                    <placeName>
                        <hi rend="italic">Manchester, Massachusetts</hi>
                    </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-08-14">
                        <hi rend="italic">August 14, 1914</hi>.</date>
                    <lb/> [<hi rend="italic">Received August 17</hi>.] </dateline>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Mr. Secretary of State</hi>: The United States Commissioner
                    of Immigration at Montreal has told the Consul of France at that city that he
                    needed authorization to let into American territory such French reservists as
                    should have to proceed individually and at their expense from Montreal to New
                    York there to take ship.</p>
                <p>I should be obliged to your excellency if you would kindly have the agent of the
                    Federal Government at Montreal instructed accordingly as soon as possible. Be
                    pleased to accept [etc.]</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_CJR1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Clausse</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
